== Roasted Vegetables ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} and @parsnip{1}(trimmed) on a diagonal into 
½-inch-thick pieces. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

Halve, peel, and mince @red onion{1} until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). 
Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Toss carrots and parsnip on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} 
and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Parmesan Mashed Potatoes ==

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. 
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Drain and return potatoes to #pot{}. Mash with 1 TBSP @butter{5%tablespoon} and @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon} 
until smooth and creamy. Stir in @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and season with salt and pepper.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Brown Butter ==

While potatoes cook, melt 2 TBSP butter (3 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #medium pan{}, preferably 
nonstick, over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until butter is foamy and 
flecked with amber brown bits, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat and carefully transfer to a #large bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Beef Tenderloin ==

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with 
salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for butter over medium-high heat. 
Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} to rest. Wash out pan.

== Shallot Pan Sauce ==

Melt 1 TBSP plain butter in same pan over medium-low heat. Add minced onion and cook until 
softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @beef demi-glace{1} and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings), and any resting 
juices from beef. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in another 
1 TBSP plain butter; season with salt and pepper.

Add carrots, parsnip, and half the parsley to bowl with brown butter; toss to thoroughly coat.

Divide veggies, mashed potatoes, and beef between plates. Top beef with pan sauce and 
remaining parsley. Serve.